Class GetPlaceTitleEvent

java.lang.Object
  com.google.gwt.event.shared.GwtEvent<GetPlaceTitleHandler>
      com.gwtplatform.mvp.client.proxy.GetPlaceTitleEvent

public class GetPlaceTitleEvent
extends GwtEvent<GetPlaceTitleHandler>

This event is fired whenever the user wants to have access to the title of a place.

Important! You should never fire that event directly. Instead, use PlaceManager.getCurrentTitle(SetPlaceTitleHandler) or PlaceManager.getTitle(int, SetPlaceTitleHandler).

Author:
Philippe Beaudoin

public static void fire(HasHandlers source,

Fires a GetPlaceTitleEvent into a source that has access to an EventBus.

Important! You should never fire that event directly. See GetPlaceTitleEvent for details.

Parameters:
source - The source that fires this event (HasHandlers).
request - The PlaceRequest for which to obtain the title.
handler - The SetPlaceTitleHandler that will be invoked when the title is obtained.
